metadata.title: Beechcraft Super King Air
aws::graph::propositions: A Beechcraft Super King Air continued to fly across Australia for five hours before crashing near Burketown in northwestern Queensland.
The Beechcraft Super King Air crash near Burketown killed all eight people on board.
The media dubbed the Beechcraft Super King Air incident the "Ghost Flight".
An investigation concluded that the occupants of the "Ghost Flight" likely became incapacitated due to hypoxia.
On January 27, 2001, a Beechcraft Super King Air 200 carrying members of the Oklahoma State University Basketball Team crashed in Colorado.
The January 27, 2001 Beechcraft Super King Air 200 crash resulted in the deaths of all 10 occupants.
On February 26, 2004, President of the Republic of Macedonia Boris Trajkovski was killed in a plane crash near Mostar.
Eight other people were killed in the crash with President Boris Trajkovski.
The plane that crashed with President Boris Trajkovski was a Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air.
The Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air was registered as Z3-BAB.
The Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air was operated as a transport aircraft of the Government of the Republic of Macedonia.
On October 24, 2004, a Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air crashed into mountainous terrain during a missed approach in Virginia.
Several members of the Hendrick Motorsports team were on board the October 24, 2004 Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air crash.
The members of the Hendrick Motorsports team died in the October 24, 2004 crash.

text:
It continued to fly across Australia for five hours before crashing near Burketown in northwestern Queensland, killing all eight on board. Dubbed the "Ghost Flight" by the media, an investigation concluded that the occupants likely became incapacitated due to hypoxia.
January 27, 2001: A Super King Air 200 carrying members of the Oklahoma State University Basketball Team crashed in Colorado, resulting in the deaths of all 10 occupants.
February 26, 2004: President of the Republic of Macedonia Boris Trajkovski was killed with eight others in the crash near Mostar. The plane was a Beechcraft Model 200 Super King Air (registered Z3-BAB) operated as a transport aircraft of the Government of the Republic of Macedonia.
October 24, 2004: A Model 200 Super King Air crashed into mountainous terrain during a missed approach in Virginia. Several members of the Hendrick Motorsports team were on board and died in the crash.
